The Manila-based International RiceResearch Institute (IRRI) said West German agriculturalscientist Klaus Lampe will take over as its director-general inearly 1988, succeeding M.S. Swaminathan.    An IRRI statement said Lampe, 56, is currently senioradviser to the German Agency for Technical Cooperation atEschborn and was a former head of the agriculture section ofthe Federal Ministry for Economic Cooperation.    It said Swaminathan, who has headed IRRI since 1982, willconcentrate on environmental and agricultural issues. REUTER&#3;